sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Creation of an Executable by an Executable
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of an executable by another executable

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a UPX-packed dropper that establishes persistence. It extracts two payloads from its resources, decodes them, and drops them as `c:\windows\addins\twain.dll` and `c:\windows\addins\taskeng.exe`. It then creates a scheduled task named `Microsoft\Windows\java\jued` using `schtasks.exe` to run the dropped `taskeng.exe` every minute with the highest privileges. Finally, it schedules its own deletion using the `at` command and a PowerShell `Remove-Item` command to cover its tracks.
